</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[188,1399,1734,1937]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Distinguished from the other genus in the subfamily, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1866" box="[844,939,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[844,939,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Voconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the smooth or corrugated surface of the head and pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[518,614,1769,1795]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1710,1736]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 3. Morphological characters. A–D. Head in dorsal view. A. Gerbelius nr. confluens. B. Voconia decorata sp. nov. C. Voconia pallidipes Stål, 1866. D. Voconia schoutedeni (Villiers, 1964) comb. nov. E–G. Head in lateral view. E. Voconia wegneri (Miller, 1954) comb. nov. F. Voconia dolichocephala sp. nov. G. Gerbelius typicus Distant, 1903. H. Voconia loki sp. nov., head and pronotum in dorsal view. I–J. Prosternum in ventrolateral view. I. Voconia mexicana sp. nov. J. Voconia bracata sp. nov. K–L. Pronotum in dorsal view. K. Voconia conradti (Jeannel, 1917) comb. nov. L. Voconia tuberculata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846642/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
); laterally flattened shape of the maxillary plates (
<figureCitation box="[1219,1315,1769,1795]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1710,1736]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 3. Morphological characters. A–D. Head in dorsal view. A. Gerbelius nr. confluens. B. Voconia decorata sp. nov. C. Voconia pallidipes Stål, 1866. D. Voconia schoutedeni (Villiers, 1964) comb. nov. E–G. Head in lateral view. E. Voconia wegneri (Miller, 1954) comb. nov. F. Voconia dolichocephala sp. nov. G. Gerbelius typicus Distant, 1903. H. Voconia loki sp. nov., head and pronotum in dorsal view. I–J. Prosternum in ventrolateral view. I. Voconia mexicana sp. nov. J. Voconia bracata sp. nov. K–L. Pronotum in dorsal view. K. Voconia conradti (Jeannel, 1917) comb. nov. L. Voconia tuberculata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846642/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); long, basally adjacent mandibular plates (
<figureCitation box="[607,701,1804,1831]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1710,1736]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 3. Morphological characters. A–D. Head in dorsal view. A. Gerbelius nr. confluens. B. Voconia decorata sp. nov. C. Voconia pallidipes Stål, 1866. D. Voconia schoutedeni (Villiers, 1964) comb. nov. E–G. Head in lateral view. E. Voconia wegneri (Miller, 1954) comb. nov. F. Voconia dolichocephala sp. nov. G. Gerbelius typicus Distant, 1903. H. Voconia loki sp. nov., head and pronotum in dorsal view. I–J. Prosternum in ventrolateral view. I. Voconia mexicana sp. nov. J. Voconia bracata sp. nov. K–L. Pronotum in dorsal view. K. Voconia conradti (Jeannel, 1917) comb. nov. L. Voconia tuberculata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846642/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); stout labium densely covered with long macrosetae on the morphologically ventral surface of labial segment I (
<figureCitation box="[809,904,1840,1866]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1710,1736]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 3. Morphological characters. A–D. Head in dorsal view. A. Gerbelius nr. confluens. B. Voconia decorata sp. nov. C. Voconia pallidipes Stål, 1866. D. Voconia schoutedeni (Villiers, 1964) comb. nov. E–G. Head in lateral view. E. Voconia wegneri (Miller, 1954) comb. nov. F. Voconia dolichocephala sp. nov. G. Gerbelius typicus Distant, 1903. H. Voconia loki sp. nov., head and pronotum in dorsal view. I–J. Prosternum in ventrolateral view. I. Voconia mexicana sp. nov. J. Voconia bracata sp. nov. K–L. Pronotum in dorsal view. K. Voconia conradti (Jeannel, 1917) comb. nov. L. Voconia tuberculata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846642/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
); morphologically dorsal surface of labial segment II 0.8–0.9 times length of labial segment I (
<figureCitation box="[830,927,1875,1901]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1710,1736]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,339,1657]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 3. Morphological characters. A–D. Head in dorsal view. A. Gerbelius nr. confluens. B. Voconia decorata sp. nov. C. Voconia pallidipes Stål, 1866. D. Voconia schoutedeni (Villiers, 1964) comb. nov. E–G. Head in lateral view. E. Voconia wegneri (Miller, 1954) comb. nov. F. Voconia dolichocephala sp. nov. G. Gerbelius typicus Distant, 1903. H. Voconia loki sp. nov., head and pronotum in dorsal view. I–J. Prosternum in ventrolateral view. I. Voconia mexicana sp. nov. J. Voconia bracata sp. nov. K–L. Pronotum in dorsal view. K. Voconia conradti (Jeannel, 1917) comb. nov. L. Voconia tuberculata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846642/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
); and Cu-An1 cell slender and tapering apically, similar in size to the M-Cu cell (
<figureCitation box="[676,771,1910,1936]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1805,1831]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,589,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-109@13.[189,1398,589,1767]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphological characters. A–D. Scutellum and hemelytron, dorsal view. A. Gerbelius typicus Distant, 1903.B. Voconia lirophleps sp. nov. C. Voconia bracata sp. nov.D. Voconia schoutedeni (Villiers, 1964) comb. nov. E. Voconia grandioculata sp. nov., thorax, lateral view. F–H. Voconia nyx sp. nov. F. Thorax, lateral view. G. Fore tibia, ventral view. H. Mid tibia and tarsus, ventral view. I–K. Hind femur, posterior view. I. Voconia mexicana sp. nov. J. Voconia decorata sp. nov. K. Voconia bracata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846644/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
